first_paragraph: I’ve been writing code since 2010, first in Python, then primarily in Go and JS/TS. I’ve spent most of my career as a backend developer and data engineer. After a couple of years leading teams of Go developers, I’m now working full-time on Boot.dev and host the Backend Banter podcast.

h1: College: A Solution in Search of a Problem
first_paragraph: College has been prescribed almost universally by the parents of the last ~40 years as the solution to life’s problems. We’ve been told it’s the way to land a good job and to make more money. But is it?
